#block(inset: (left: 20pt), below: 0.3em)[#text(size: 8.5pt, fill: rgb("#2d3748"))[Frameworks whose differentiator is execution efficiency rather than abstractions for authoring agents. Covers parallel dispatch, batching, and cost/latency tradeoffs.]]
#block(above: 0.6em, below: 0.2em, inset: (left: 24pt))[#text(size: 10.5pt, weight: "bold", fill: rgb("#4a5568"))[]]
#block(inset: (left: 32pt), below: 0.2em)[#text(size: 9pt, style: "italic", fill: rgb("#4a5568"))[Frameworks that parallelise agent or subtask execution across workers for throughput.]]
#block(inset: (left: 32pt), below: 0.3em)[#text(size: 8.5pt, fill: rgb("#2d3748"))[Tools that fan out agent work — steps, tool calls, or whole agent runs — across parallel workers. Targets throughput-bound workloads where serial agent loops are the bottleneck.]]
#block(inset: (left: 32pt), below: 0.4em)[#text(size: 8.5pt, fill: rgb("#2f855a"))[*Examples:* EnsoAI]]
#block(above: 0.8em, below: 0.3em, inset: (left: 12pt))[#text(size: 12pt, weight: "bold", fill: rgb("#2b6cb0"))[]]
#block(inset: (left: 20pt), below: 0.2em)[#text(size: 9pt, style: "italic", fill: rgb("#4a5568"))[Frameworks for simulating populations of agents modelling social, economic, or behavioural dynamics.]]
#block(inset: (left: 20pt), below: 0.3em)[#text(size: 8.5pt, fill: rgb("#2d3748"))[Frameworks for agent-based social simulation: many LLM-backed personas interacting under rules to study emergent group behaviour. Used for research, game-like worlds, and counterfactual studies rather than task execution.]]
#block(inset: (left: 20pt), below: 0.4em)[#text(size: 8.5pt, fill: rgb("#2f855a"))[*Examples:* Concordia, Moltbook]]
#block(above: 0.8em, below: 0.3em, inset: (left: 12pt))[#text(size: 12pt, weight: "bold", fill: rgb("#2b6cb0"))[]]
#block(inset: (left: 20pt), below: 0.2em)[#text(size: 9pt, style: "italic", fill: rgb("#4a5568"))[Frameworks built around persistent, long-lived agent state and memory as the core abstraction.]]
#block(inset: (left: 20pt), below: 0.3em)[#text(size: 8.5pt, fill: rgb("#2d3748"))[Frameworks where durable agent state — memory, identity, long-running context — is the central primitive rather than a bolt-on. Agents persist across sessions and evolve their internal state over time.]]
