#block(inset: (left: 20pt), below: 0.2em)[#text(size: 9pt, style: "italic", fill: rgb("#4a5568"))[Web or desktop chat interfaces purpose-built as frontends for agents rather than plain LLMs.]]
#block(inset: (left: 20pt), below: 0.3em)[#text(size: 8.5pt, fill: rgb("#2d3748"))[Chat-style user interfaces tailored for agent interaction — tool call rendering, step traces, artefact display — rather than generic LLM chat. Typically web-based and framework-agnostic on the backend.]]
